.TH "virtio_pci_find_capability" 9 "virtio_pci_find_capability" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
virtio_pci_find_capability \- walk capabilities to find device info.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" virtio_pci_find_capability
.BI "(struct pci_dev *dev "  ","
.BI "u8 cfg_type "  ","
.BI "u32 ioresource_types "  ","
.BI "int *bars "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
the pci device
.IP "cfg_type" 12
the VIRTIO_PCI_CAP_* value we seek
.IP "ioresource_types" 12
IORESOURCE_MEM and/or IORESOURCE_IO.
.IP "bars" 12
the bitmask of BARs
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns offset of the capability, or 0.
